ds through the political transformations of the 1980s, the local activism of the 1990s, and spreads through Guédiguian's diverse experimentation with genres and registers. It emphasises Guédiguian's political assessments and his frequent meditations on history, violence, and utopia. But it returns consistently to the underlying themes of friendship, and thus intervenes at the crossroads of affect, politics, philosophy, and art.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFriendship in motion pictures. 0aMotion pictures, FrenchxHistory. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aAuteur Studies.  aCinema Studies.  aFrench Cinema.  aFrench Studies.  aLocal Politics.  aPerformance.  aPhilosophy of Friendship.  aPolitics of Friendship.  aUtopianism.1 aMai, Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2017 eBook-Packagez978311128281740uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152610777040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526107770423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526107770/original  a978-3-11-128281-7  Manchester University Press 2017 eBook-Packageb2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles